data.text:
Julie Clark Music was the first record label used for Baby Einstein's CD's. It was formed in December 1997 by Julie Aigner-Clark as the music distribution division of I Think I Can Productions, which was later renamed to Aigner-Clark Productions in October 1998, which was too renamed to The Baby Einstein Company in February 1999. On October 31, 1999, ten days after the release of the Bedtime Classics 1999 CD, it was rebranded as and succeeded by Baby Einstein Music. In 2000, Baby Mozart, Baby Bach, Baby Beethoven and Bedtime Classics were reissued, recomposed and redistributed under the Baby Einstein Music label.
